webpackJsonp([65380673165540],{1285:function(e,A){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Psyked: James' Web Development website",author:"James Ford"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/James/Repositories/portfolio-2018/src/posts/simple-box2d-better-cleverer-more-optimised/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/box2d-shapes-2-e52dcb46a0a91c49c1d0d8427cce3475-e8574.jpg"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 55.99999999999999%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/jpeg;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="box2d shapes 2"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/box2d-shapes-2-e52dcb46a0a91c49c1d0d8427cce3475-e8574.jpg"\n        srcset="/static/box2d-shapes-2-e52dcb46a0a91c49c1d0d8427cce3475-c94d9.jpg 158w,\n/static/box2d-shapes-2-e52dcb46a0a91c49c1d0d8427cce3475-9885b.jpg 315w,\n/static/box2d-shapes-2-e52dcb46a0a91c49c1d0d8427cce3475-e8574.jpg 500w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p><em>^ This time, that\'s an image - saves on the page rendering time!</em></p>\n<p>Another update on the Box2D classes I\'m working on.  No new features, but some pretty cool expansions and improvements to the library object creation.</p>\n<p>If you check out <a href="http://www.psyked.co.uk/box2d/demo-source-simple-box2d-with-curved-edges.htm">the previous post</a>, you\'ll see that the the dynamically drawn shapes weren\'t exactly perfect; nor were they very efficient.  Oh they worked fine, and traced the detail of the shape very well - but it took a decent chunk of system resources to animate and ended up with some overlaid shapes; which all made the Box2D a bit sluggish and the behaviours buggy.</p>\n<p>So, stealing incorporating ideas from other projects has been the name of the game - namely the ear clipping optimisation code from <a href="http://www.splashdust.net/2009/10/box2d-mouse-drawing-now-with-ear-clipping/">Splashdust.net</a>, combined with some of my own cobbled-together more optimised code for tracing curved edges.</p>\n<h3>Live demo:</h3>\n<p>Mouse interaction is enabled in the below example - click and drag the objects to check out how it works.</p>\n<p>[kml_flashembed movie="<a href="http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/LettersExperiment.swf">http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/LettersExperiment.swf</a>" height="280" width="500" /]</p>\n<h3><a href="http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/simplebox2d_demo_100202.zip">Download the source code for this demo.</a></h3>\n<p>* The source code isn\'t exactly cleaned up - sometime, eventually, it will be.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Simple Box2D - Better, cleverer, more optimised.",date:"February 03, 2010",tags:["box2d","actionscript"],url:null,image:null,description:null}}},pathContext:{prev:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/fixed-air-update-framework-broken/",tags:["air-update-framework","flex-3-5-sdk"],title:"Fixed: AIR update framework broken!",date:"2010-01-29T21:30:30.000Z",description:null,image:null}},next:{frontmatter:{path:"/blog/minimal-components-for-when-you-dont-feel-like-using-flex/",tags:["flash","minimalcomps"],title:"Minimal components: For when you don't feel like using Flex.",date:"2010-02-23T08:45:11.000Z",description:null,image:null}}}}}});
